Diagnostic.Title: Assemblys mit Assemblyversion markieren
Diagnostic.Description: Das .NET Framework verwendet die Versionsnummer zur eindeutigen Identifikation einer Assembly und zum Binden an Typen in Assemblys mit starker Namensgebung. Die Versionsnummer wird zusammen mit der Versions- und Herausgeberrichtlinie verwendet. Standardmäßig werden Anwendungen nur mit der Assemblyversion ausgeführt, mit der sie erstellt wurden.

Diagnostic.Title: Member als statisch markieren
Diagnostic.Description: Member, die nicht auf Instanzdaten zugreifen oder Instanzmethoden aufrufen, können als "static" markiert werden. Nachdem Sie die Methoden als statisch markiert haben, gibt der Compiler nicht virtuelle Aufrufsites an diese Member aus. Dadurch kann sich für leistungsabhängigen Code eine spürbare Leistungssteigerung ergeben.

Diagnostic.Title: Dereferenzierung eines möglichen Nullverweises.
Code should not contain trailing whitespace
Diagnostic.Description: There should not be any whitespace at the end of a line of code.

Diagnostic.Title: Prefix local calls with this
Diagnostic.Description: A call to an instance member of the local class or a base class is not prefixed with 'this.', within a C# code file.

Diagnostic.Title: Split parameters should start on line after declaration
Diagnostic.Description: The parameters to a C# method or indexer call or declaration span across multiple lines, but the first parameter does not start on the line after the opening bracket.

Diagnostic.Title: Elements should have the same indentation
Diagnostic.Description: Elements at the same level in the syntax tree should have the same indentation.

Diagnostic.Title: Using directives should be placed correctly
Diagnostic.Description: A C# using directive is placed outside of a namespace element.

Diagnostic.Title: Elements should appear in the correct order
Diagnostic.Description: An element within a C# code file is out of order in relation to the other elements in the code.

Diagnostic.Title: System using directives should be placed before other using directives
Diagnostic.Description: A using directive which declares a member of the 'System' namespace appears after a using directive which declares a member of a different namespace, within a C# code file.

Diagnostic.Title: Using alias directives should be placed after other using directives
Diagnostic.Description: A using-alias directive is positioned before a regular using directive.

Diagnostic.Title: Using directives should be ordered alphabetically by namespace
Diagnostic.Description: The using directives within a C# code file are not sorted alphabetically by namespace.

Diagnostic.Title: Element should begin with upper-case letter
Diagnostic.Description: The name of a C# element does not begin with an upper-case letter.

Diagnostic.Title: Field names should not begin with underscore
Diagnostic.Description: A field name in C# begins with an underscore.

Diagnostic.Title: Opening braces should not be preceded by blank line
Diagnostic.Description: An opening brace within a C# element, statement, or expression is preceded by a blank line.

Diagnostic.Title: Single-line comments should not be followed by blank line
Diagnostic.Description: A single-line comment within C# code is followed by a blank line.

Diagnostic.Title: Closing brace should be followed by blank line
Diagnostic.Description: A closing brace within a C# element, statement, or expression is not followed by a blank line.

Diagnostic.Title: Element documentation header should be preceded by blank line
Diagnostic.Description: An element documentation header above a C# element is not preceded by a blank line.

Diagnostic.Title: Elements should be separated by blank line
Diagnostic.Description: Adjacent C# elements are not separated by a blank line.

Diagnostic.Title: Elements should be documented
Diagnostic.Description: A C# code element is missing a documentation header.

Diagnostic.Title: Element parameters should be documented
Diagnostic.Description: A C# method, constructor, delegate or indexer element is missing documentation for one or more of its parameters.

Diagnostic.Title: Element return value should be documented
Diagnostic.Description: A C# element is missing documentation for its return value.

Diagnostic.Title: Property summary documentation should match accessors
Diagnostic.Description: The documentation text within a C# property’s <summary> tag does not match the accessors within the property.

Diagnostic.Title: File should have header
Diagnostic.Description: A C# code file is missing a standard file header.

Diagnostic.Title: inheritdoc should be used with inheriting class
Diagnostic.Description: <inheritdoc> has been used on an element that doesn't inherit from a base class or implement an interface.
